{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LowQgcrq4ZeHuMQF1bS1oc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. The config has:\n- `discovery.seed_hosts` - set correctly with all 3 nodes\n- `cluster.initial_master_nodes` - MISSING\n\nFor ES 7.x, a fresh cluster (no prior cluster state) requires `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to be set so that the cluster can bootstrap. The nodes can find each other via `discovery.seed_hosts`, but they can't elect a master without knowing which nodes are eligible to be initial masters.\nThe fix involves adding `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to the configmap and restarting the pods, then removing it once the cluster forms and doing a rolling restart to verify stability without it. setting. The key insight is that `subPath` mounts don't automatically propagate configmap updates to running pods, so I need to explicitly restart them after patching the configmap. Once the cluster forms and persists its state, I can safely remove the bootstrap setting and do a final rolling restart to confirm stability. the step where I need to decide on the restart strategy. Since there's no active cluster yet, I could delete all pods simultaneously for speed, but a rolling restart is safer and aligns with the goal of maintaining cluster health once it's formed. I can see the configmap is using `subPath` for the mount, which means changes won't automatically propagate to running pods—they need to be restarted. My plan is to patch the configmap with `cluster.initial_master_nodes`, delete all pods at once to let them come up with the new config, wait for the cluster to stabilize, then remove that bootstrap setting and do a rolling restart to verify everything stays healthy.\n\nFor checking cluster health during this process, I'll use the curl-test pod to query the Elasticsearch API and confirm the cluster is in a good state.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":667,"cache_read_input_tokens":40098,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":667},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"abbddbdc-f03e-4cd7-b389-d5d620cc9cdd","uuid":"7e00babd-952d-43e8-8db6-1ae00ff40f83","request_id":"req_011Ccfd6BhcfxQBf3BjmMchF"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LowQgcrq4ZeHuMQF1bS1oc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The problem is clear: `cluster.initial_master_nodes` is missing from the configmap. ES 7.x needs this to bootstrap master election on a fresh cluster. The nodes can discover each other but can't elect a master without it.\n\n**Plan:**\n1. Add `cluster.initial_master_nodes` to the configmap\n2. Delete all pods so they restart with the new config (no live data yet)\n3. Wait for cluster to form and go healthy\n4. Remove `cluster.initial_master_nodes` (it's bootstrap-only and dangerous to leave)\n5. Rolling restart to prove the cluster stays healthy without it\n\n**Phase 1 — Patch the configmap and bootstrap the cluster:**"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":667,"cache_read_input_tokens":40098,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":667},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"abbddbdc-f03e-4cd7-b389-d5d620cc9cdd","uuid":"11db6b17-3438-42b9-ab76-20811af6d5fe","request_id":"req_011Ccfd6BhcfxQBf3BjmMchF"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LowQgcrq4ZeHuMQF1bS1oc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01CWgctdVWmqPNDSQfGhVDrX","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl patch configmap es-config -n elasticsearch --patch '\ndata:\n  elasticsearch.yml: |\n    cluster.name: es-cluster\n    node.name: ${POD_NAME}\n    node.roles: [ master, data, ingest ]\n    network.host: 0.0.0.0\n    discovery.seed_hosts:\n      - es-cluster-0.es-cluster\n      - es-cluster-1.es-cluster\n      - es-cluster-2.es-cluster\n    cluster.initial_master_nodes:\n      - es-cluster-0\n      - es-cluster-1\n      - es-cluster-2\n    node.store.allow_mmap: false\n'","description":"Add cluster.initial_master_nodes to the elasticsearch configmap"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":667,"cache_read_input_tokens":40098,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":667},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"abbddbdc-f03e-4cd7-b389-d5d620cc9cdd","uuid":"d88066f4-b1b3-47f5-abe5-ba9db62e8e31","request_id":"req_011Ccfd6BhcfxQBf3BjmMchF"}
